# The `FileWriter` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

A simplified binary data writer class that doesn&#39;t require targets, target definitions, architectures, or require any other optional compile time libraries to be enabled via the build process. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

A simplified binary data writer class that doesn&#39;t require targets, target definitions, architectures, or require any other optional compile time libraries to be enabled via the build process.

This class needs the ability to seek to different spots in the binary stream that is produces to fixup offsets and sizes.

Definition at line 29 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/gsym/filewriter-h">FileWriter.h</a>.

### fixup32() {#a23334fee66fedcc03e7c74ed4295611c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void FileWriter::fixup32 (uint32&#95;t Value, uint64&#95;t Offset)</>}>
Fixup a uint32&#95;t value at the specified offset in the stream.

This function will save the current file position, seek to the specified offset, overwrite the data using <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a>, and then restore the file position to the previous file position.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="<a href=&quot;/docs/api/classes/llvm/value&quot;>Value</a>">The value to write into the stream.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Offset">The offset at which to write the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> within the stream.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

### writeNullTerminated() {#acbe1d7578ceb2fd20d24412def14805d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void FileWriter::writeNullTerminated (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">llvm::StringRef</a> Str)</>}>
Write a NULL terminated C string into the stream at the current file position.

The entire contents of Str will be written into the steam at the current file position and then an extra NULL termation byte will be written. It is up to the user to ensure that Str doesn&#39;t contain any NULL characters unless the additional NULL characters are desired.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Str">The value to write into the stream.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>
